Product Notes

Not only was Connie Francis one of the biggest recording stars in the English-speaking world, she also triumphed in many other foreign countries such as Germany, France and Japan. Consequently her record label had her make discs of her hits in languages such as German, French and Japanese, and on this release we feature 26 tracks of Connie singing in nine languages, many of them becoming major hits in those countries. On this CD you will hear Connie sing "Vacation" in Japanese, "Where the Boys Are in Spanish", "Mr Twister" in French and "Don't Break the Heart That Loves You" in German. Many tracks here are appearing on CD for the first time.
